cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.EC, cs.NE 

This paper is about designing an incentive compatible auction using a neural network approach. The problem is related to game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves designing a learning algorithm for the auction. The use of neural networks also suggests the paper could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with economic aspects of the auction design, which falls under the category of computational economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper proposes a new neural architecture for the auction design problem, which could be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE).
